  "prompt": "How can I transfer from an international university to a US university as a US permanent resident?",
  "response": "Transferring from an international university to a U.S. university as a U.S. permanent resident involves several steps. Here\u2019s a comprehensive guide to help you through the process:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Research U.S. Universities**\n- Identify universities that offer your desired program.\n- Check their transfer policies, especially for international students and permanent residents.\n- Ensure the university accepts transfer students and meets your academic and personal needs.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Understand Transfer Requirements**\n- **Transfer Credits:** Contact the admissions office to determine if credits from your international university will transfer. Some schools may require a course-by-course evaluation from a credential evaluation service (e.g., WES, ECE).\n- **GPA Requirements:** Check the minimum GPA needed for transfer admission.\n- **Prerequisite Courses:** Ensure you\u2019ve completed required courses for your intended major.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Prepare Application Materials**\n- **Transcripts:** Request official transcripts from your current university, translated into English if necessary.\n- **Test Scores:** Some universities may require SAT, ACT, or English proficiency tests (e.g., TOEFL, IELTS) if your previous education was not in English.\n- **Letters of Recommendation:** Obtain letters from professors or advisors who can vouch for your academic abilities.\n- **Personal Statement/Essay:** Write a compelling statement explaining why you want to transfer and how the U.S. university aligns with your goals.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Financial Planning**\n- Check tuition and living costs at your target universities.\n- Explore financial aid options for permanent residents, such as federal student loans, scholarships, and grants.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Submit Applications**\n- Complete the application form for each university.\n- Pay the application fees.\n- Submit all required documents by the deadlines.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Maintain Legal Status**\n- As a permanent resident, ensure your Green Card is valid and you meet residency requirements.\n- Notify USCIS if you relocate to the U.S. for school.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Apply for a Student Visa (if needed)**\n- If you\u2019re studying abroad temporarily, you may need an F-1 visa to return to the U.S. Check with the U.S. embassy in your current country.\n\n---\n\n### **8. Plan Your Move**\n- Once accepted, arrange for housing, health insurance, and other essentials.\n- Attend orientation programs to acclimate to the new university.\n\n---\n\n### **Tips for Success**\n- Communicate regularly with the admissions office to clarify any doubts.\n- Start the process early to ensure you meet all deadlines.\n- Seek guidance from academic advisors or transfer counselors.\n\nBy following these steps, you can successfully transfer from an international university to a U.S. university as a permanent resident. Good luck!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
